The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 December is 145,457 (16,764.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 December, there were 9,411 new confirmed cases (1,084.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 December, there were 7,135 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 32% (2,276 extra cases).
